title: How to Fry Breaded Chicken Strips

steps.headline: Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F (190 degrees C).
Make breadcrumbs.
Place the breadcrumbs, eggs and flour in 3 separate shallow dishes.
Pound the chicken breasts.
steps.description: Learn how: how to pound out a chicken breast.

steps.headline: Slice the chicken into 1 ⁄2 inch (3.8 cm) strips.
Coat the chicken strips with a light coat of flour.
Heat 1/4 in.
steps.description: of oil in a large skillet over medium heat. The oil is hot enough when a small drop of water "dances" or "pops" when added to the hot oil.

steps.headline: Place 2-3 chicken strips in the pan simultaneously.
Fry for 2 minutes.
steps.description: Do not flip the strips during this time.

steps.headline: Flip the chicken strips.
steps.description: Fry for 2-3 minutes until they are golden brown.

steps.headline: Remove from the frying pan onto paper towels to absorb the excess oil.
Continue to fry the chicken strips as directed.

"} Heat 1/4 in. of oil in a large skillet over medium heat. The oil is hot enough when a small drop of water "dances" or "pops" when added to the hot oil. Place 2-3 chicken strips in the pan simultaneously. Fry for 2 minutes. Do not flip the strips during this time. Flip the chicken strips. Fry for 2-3 minutes until they are golden brown. Remove from the frying pan onto paper towels to absorb the excess oil. Continue to fry the chicken strips as directed. Serve.
